BimiTool  1.2
=============

This program is designed for people who manage the beverages in a
dormitory or flat-sharing community. It is assumed that inhabiters
use tally marks to record how many drinks they had.  For the time
beeing there is no web-interface or client available.

==== Anmerkungen Johannes ====

Quellcode: https://github.com/johannes87/bimiTool
Basiert auf: https://github.com/KapuKapu/bimiTool (danke @ nefarius)

Windows-Installation:
---------------------

* Python2 installieren: https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/ ("Latest Python 2 Release"). Bei der Installation auswählen, dass python.exe im PATH installiert werden soll.

* In Windows ausloggen und wieder einloggen, damit python.exe im PATH gefunden wird.

* PyGObject installieren: https://wiki.gnome.org/action/show/Projects/PyGObject ("Windows isntallers with Gtk3 support", z.B. "pygi-aio-3.18.2_rev3-setup.exe"). Bei der Installation "GTK+" auswählen.

* PyYAML installieren: Auf Kommandozeile eingeben: python.exe -m pip install pyyaml

* bimiTool.cmd starten ;)

Features
--------
* add/delete/edit accounts and drinks
* add/delete transactions, ie. consume drinks and add credit/debit
* generate mail text with account and balance listing


Dependencies
------------
* Python (tested with version 2.6, 2.7)
* Python GTK+3 bindings ( >=gir1.2-gtk-3.0 )
* Python SQLite3 bindings (pysqlite2)


Installing
----------
BimiTool can be started without installing by simply running
bimiTool.py


Removing
--------
Delete the folder containing the BimiTool.


